{
  "stem": "24409.12",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And once a year, I went to a two-weeks training mission, which consisted in my being, [? you ?] [? see, ?] working as a psychologist at the Walter Reed Army Hospital, just consulted in psychotherapy, or at the Naval Hospital in Bethesda for two weeks once a year.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when I became 60 years old, which was in 1966, I was transferred to the-- to the retired reserve.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- first of all, I started-- I went to Columbia University to get an American degree because I was-- knew a lot about psychology.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But psychology was entirely different here than in Europe.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Europeans psychologists saw the American psychologist as somebody who takes a rat and weighs the feces of the rat.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then four weeks later, he weighs it again.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's ?] [? a ?] [? difference ?] [? in ?] [? psychology, ?] [?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I said. ?] But the American psychology saw the European psychologist as someone who's sitting back on a chair while-- while a patient tells his story, and he reads a book.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I had to Americanize my outlook.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I went to Columbia, and I attended a lot of classes at Columbia very intensively for about one year.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And after the year, I found myself on a bulletin board because I qualified for the [INAUDIBLE], which I took in this year for their master's examination, comprehensive master's examination.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I took it and made a [INAUDIBLE] and got a master's degree from Columbia in psychology.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then I was in private practice for a short time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I-- we lived in Maryland.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I did some counseling there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I was the still quite unsure of my capacities in psychology.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And when the Korean War came, I became chief psychologist in Leavenworth.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
